text.section:
Each life insurer, nonprofit health service plan, and fraternal benefit society that does business in the State shall submit annually the opinion of a qualified actuary as to whether the reserves and related actuarial items held in support of the life insurer's policies, contracts, and benefit agreements are:
computed appropriately;
based on assumptions that satisfy contractual provisions;
consistent with prior reported amounts; and
in compliance with applicable laws of the State.
